what is your biggest joy in life my biggest joy in life would have to be the fact that i am taking care of my health failing parents after the unexpected death of my only brother both of my parents took a bad turn in their health they just couldn't deal with his death so i gave up my job and home to come be with them even their daughter in law wouldn't come to stay with them nor would their own grand kids that lived right next door to them i let my parents do what they can by their self but i am right there if they should need me for anything at all the way i look at it is they took care of me for years or so and now it is my turn to take care of them they are my joys in life as well as my own kids these will be the only parents that i will ever have so i am going to enjoy them now while i still have them around One Tree Hill (TV series) The Life and Times of Juniper Lee About a Boy Charmed Joy (novel) The Fairly OddParents Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Hikikomori Humphrey Bogart Dead Like Me Kyle Broflovski Divorce Baby Blues Invader Zim Jane Wyman The Isley Brothers The Catcher in the Rye Polyamory The Joy Luck Club Joy Division (band) Trailer Park Boys Murdock-Portal Elementary School Good Times EastEnders Infantilism Bill Gaither Fancy Crane Shaggy dog story Saved by the Bell Knots Landing Pitaten Theory of conduct Blood on the Tracks Order of succession Rocko's Modern Life K' Code: Lyoko Pok__mon Chronicles True Crime: Streets of LA Childbirth Final Fantasy: Unlimited Wolfrider Lemony Snicket's A Series of Unfortunate Events Melanie Wilkes Hillary Rodham Clinton Everybody Loves Raymond Marvin Gaye Recess (TV series) Lunar: Silver Star Story Complete Kate Vaiden Chris Benoit Days of our Lives Laura Schlessinger George VI of the United Kingdom South Park Gothic rock Timmy Turner Doug For Better or For Worse 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Vegeta Mary, the mother of Jesus Hollyoaks Lou Gehrig The Magic School Bus Great Teacher Onizuka Kodocha Garfield Gry